Upon successful completion of this course, students should be able to

1. Articulate points of synthesis and integration between different areas of theological studies;

2. Direct their understanding towards the new set of questions and insight in relation to the chosen project;

3. Present integrated theological ideas coherently, creatively and effectively, taking into account critical feedback from peers;

4. Plan and execute a substantial integrative project with a critical evaluation.

